<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="197" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="197">Measurements.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="197">
Total length: male 3.0-3.5 mm (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">N</emphasis>
= 4), female 5.1 mm (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">N</emphasis>
= 1).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="197" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="197">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="197">
The salient features of the new species include: general color (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 1–8" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 8. Metanigrus chromus sp. nov., male 1 dorsal view 2 lateral view. Metanigrus guttatus sp. nov., male 3 dorsal view 4 lateral view. Metanigrus gremius sp. nov., male 5 dorsal view 6 lateral view. Metanigrus spinatus sp. nov., male 7 dorsal view 8 lateral view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1024.62226.figures1-8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/520803" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">5</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 1–8" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 8. Metanigrus chromus sp. nov., male 1 dorsal view 2 lateral view. Metanigrus guttatus sp. nov., male 3 dorsal view 4 lateral view. Metanigrus gremius sp. nov., male 5 dorsal view 6 lateral view. Metanigrus spinatus sp. nov., male 7 dorsal view 8 lateral view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1024.62226.figures1-8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/520803" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">6</figureCitation>
) yellowish white; dorsolateral and middle parts of anal tube (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 31–41" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 31 - 41. Metanigrus gremius sp. nov., male 31 head and thorax, dorsal view 32 frons, ventral view 33 tegmina 34 wing 35, 38 pygofer, lateral view 36, 39 gonostyli and pygofer, ventral view 37 aedeagus, left lateral view 40 gonostyli, dorsal view 41 aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1024.62226.figures31-41" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/520806" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">35</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 31–41" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 31 - 41. Metanigrus gremius sp. nov., male 31 head and thorax, dorsal view 32 frons, ventral view 33 tegmina 34 wing 35, 38 pygofer, lateral view 36, 39 gonostyli and pygofer, ventral view 37 aedeagus, left lateral view 40 gonostyli, dorsal view 41 aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1024.62226.figures31-41" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/520806" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">38</figureCitation>
) each with a finger-like process; outer process of gonostyli (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 31–41" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 31 - 41. Metanigrus gremius sp. nov., male 31 head and thorax, dorsal view 32 frons, ventral view 33 tegmina 34 wing 35, 38 pygofer, lateral view 36, 39 gonostyli and pygofer, ventral view 37 aedeagus, left lateral view 40 gonostyli, dorsal view 41 aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1024.62226.figures31-41" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/520806" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">35</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 31–41" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 31 - 41. Metanigrus gremius sp. nov., male 31 head and thorax, dorsal view 32 frons, ventral view 33 tegmina 34 wing 35, 38 pygofer, lateral view 36, 39 gonostyli and pygofer, ventral view 37 aedeagus, left lateral view 40 gonostyli, dorsal view 41 aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1024.62226.figures31-41" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/520806" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">38</figureCitation>
) convex and arcuate with nearly square process at apex in lateral view.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="197" type="coloration">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="197">Coloration.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="197">
General color yellowish white (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 1–8" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 8. Metanigrus chromus sp. nov., male 1 dorsal view 2 lateral view. Metanigrus guttatus sp. nov., male 3 dorsal view 4 lateral view. Metanigrus gremius sp. nov., male 5 dorsal view 6 lateral view. Metanigrus spinatus sp. nov., male 7 dorsal view 8 lateral view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1024.62226.figures1-8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/520803" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">5</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 1–8" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 8. Metanigrus chromus sp. nov., male 1 dorsal view 2 lateral view. Metanigrus guttatus sp. nov., male 3 dorsal view 4 lateral view. Metanigrus gremius sp. nov., male 5 dorsal view 6 lateral view. Metanigrus spinatus sp. nov., male 7 dorsal view 8 lateral view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1024.62226.figures1-8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/520803" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">6</figureCitation>
). Mesonotum light brown. Eyes black. Legs yellowish brown. Tegmina semitransparent. Wings hyaline. Abdomen yellowish white.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="197" type="head and thorax">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="197">Head and thorax.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="197">
Head (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 1–8" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 8. Metanigrus chromus sp. nov., male 1 dorsal view 2 lateral view. Metanigrus guttatus sp. nov., male 3 dorsal view 4 lateral view. Metanigrus gremius sp. nov., male 5 dorsal view 6 lateral view. Metanigrus spinatus sp. nov., male 7 dorsal view 8 lateral view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1024.62226.figures1-8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/520803" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">5</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 31–41" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 31 - 41. Metanigrus gremius sp. nov., male 31 head and thorax, dorsal view 32 frons, ventral view 33 tegmina 34 wing 35, 38 pygofer, lateral view 36, 39 gonostyli and pygofer, ventral view 37 aedeagus, left lateral view 40 gonostyli, dorsal view 41 aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1024.62226.figures31-41" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/520806" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">31</figureCitation>
) significantly narrower than pronotum, without median carina. Vertex shorter in middle line than wide at base (1: 1.99), with two posterolateral areolets at base not meeting medially. Frons (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 31–41" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 31 - 41. Metanigrus gremius sp. nov., male 31 head and thorax, dorsal view 32 frons, ventral view 33 tegmina 34 wing 35, 38 pygofer, lateral view 36, 39 gonostyli and pygofer, ventral view 37 aedeagus, left lateral view 40 gonostyli, dorsal view 41 aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1024.62226.figures31-41" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/520806" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">32</figureCitation>
) subrectangular, without median carina, longer in middle line than wide at widest portion (about 1.93: 1), lateral carinae with a dense row of sensory pits along outer margin. Postclypeus (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 31–41" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 31 - 41. Metanigrus gremius sp. nov., male 31 head and thorax, dorsal view 32 frons, ventral view 33 tegmina 34 wing 35, 38 pygofer, lateral view 36, 39 gonostyli and pygofer, ventral view 37 aedeagus, left lateral view 40 gonostyli, dorsal view 41 aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1024.62226.figures31-41" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/520806" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">32</figureCitation>
) with distinct median and lateral carinae. Frontoclypeal suture nearly straight. Rostrum elongate, surpassing hind-coxae. Pronotum (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 31–41" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 31 - 41. Metanigrus gremius sp. nov., male 31 head and thorax, dorsal view 32 frons, ventral view 33 tegmina 34 wing 35, 38 pygofer, lateral view 36, 39 gonostyli and pygofer, ventral view 37 aedeagus, left lateral view 40 gonostyli, dorsal view 41 aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1024.62226.figures31-41" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/520806" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">31</figureCitation>
) wider than maximum width of head (including eyes) (1.43: 1), with median carina and sinuate lateral carinae. Mesonotum (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 31–41" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 31 - 41. Metanigrus gremius sp. nov., male 31 head and thorax, dorsal view 32 frons, ventral view 33 tegmina 34 wing 35, 38 pygofer, lateral view 36, 39 gonostyli and pygofer, ventral view 37 aedeagus, left lateral view 40 gonostyli, dorsal view 41 aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1024.62226.figures31-41" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/520806" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">31</figureCitation>
) about 5.96 times longer than pronotum in midline, with distinct median carina. Tegmina (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 31–41" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 31 - 41. Metanigrus gremius sp. nov., male 31 head and thorax, dorsal view 32 frons, ventral view 33 tegmina 34 wing 35, 38 pygofer, lateral view 36, 39 gonostyli and pygofer, ventral view 37 aedeagus, left lateral view 40 gonostyli, dorsal view 41 aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1024.62226.figures31-41" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/520806" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">33</figureCitation>
) slender, longer than maximal width (2.59: 1), almost as wide at postnodal as prenodal area, veins ScP + 
<collectionCode country="Chile" name="Departamento de Geologia, Universidad de Chile">R</collectionCode>
+ 
<collectionCode country="0" name="Mohonk Preserve, Inc.">MP</collectionCode>
with several sensory pits, 
<collectionCode country="0" name="Mohonk Preserve, Inc.">MP</collectionCode>
3 two branched; five postnodal closed cells with C1 smaller than C2, C5 placed next to C3, C4 distally displaced after the nodal line, im, r-m and anterior two-thirds of margin with white areas. Hind wing (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 31–41" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 31 - 41. Metanigrus gremius sp. nov., male 31 head and thorax, dorsal view 32 frons, ventral view 33 tegmina 34 wing 35, 38 pygofer, lateral view 36, 39 gonostyli and pygofer, ventral view 37 aedeagus, left lateral view 40 gonostyli, dorsal view 41 aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1024.62226.figures31-41" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/520806" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">34</figureCitation>
) with lateral margin notched at CuA1, CuP, and A2, more strongly at A1; A2 not reaching posterior margin. Metatibiotarsal formula: (3+5)-6-5.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="197" type="male genitalia">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="197">Male genitalia.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="197">
Pygofer (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 31–41" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 31 - 41. Metanigrus gremius sp. nov., male 31 head and thorax, dorsal view 32 frons, ventral view 33 tegmina 34 wing 35, 38 pygofer, lateral view 36, 39 gonostyli and pygofer, ventral view 37 aedeagus, left lateral view 40 gonostyli, dorsal view 41 aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1024.62226.figures31-41" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/520806" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">35</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 31–41" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 31 - 41. Metanigrus gremius sp. nov., male 31 head and thorax, dorsal view 32 frons, ventral view 33 tegmina 34 wing 35, 38 pygofer, lateral view 36, 39 gonostyli and pygofer, ventral view 37 aedeagus, left lateral view 40 gonostyli, dorsal view 41 aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1024.62226.figures31-41" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/520806" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">36</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 31–41" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 31 - 41. Metanigrus gremius sp. nov., male 31 head and thorax, dorsal view 32 frons, ventral view 33 tegmina 34 wing 35, 38 pygofer, lateral view 36, 39 gonostyli and pygofer, ventral view 37 aedeagus, left lateral view 40 gonostyli, dorsal view 41 aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1024.62226.figures31-41" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/520806" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">38</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 31–41" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 31 - 41. Metanigrus gremius sp. nov., male 31 head and thorax, dorsal view 32 frons, ventral view 33 tegmina 34 wing 35, 38 pygofer, lateral view 36, 39 gonostyli and pygofer, ventral view 37 aedeagus, left lateral view 40 gonostyli, dorsal view 41 aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1024.62226.figures31-41" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/520806" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">39</figureCitation>
) symmetrical, gradually narrowed towards the apex, with sinuate anterior and posterior margins. Pygopher with internal sulcus and slightly curved lateral margins in ventral view. Anal tube (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 31–41" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 31 - 41. Metanigrus gremius sp. nov., male 31 head and thorax, dorsal view 32 frons, ventral view 33 tegmina 34 wing 35, 38 pygofer, lateral view 36, 39 gonostyli and pygofer, ventral view 37 aedeagus, left lateral view 40 gonostyli, dorsal view 41 aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1024.62226.figures31-41" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/520806" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">35</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 31–41" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 31 - 41. Metanigrus gremius sp. nov., male 31 head and thorax, dorsal view 32 frons, ventral view 33 tegmina 34 wing 35, 38 pygofer, lateral view 36, 39 gonostyli and pygofer, ventral view 37 aedeagus, left lateral view 40 gonostyli, dorsal view 41 aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1024.62226.figures31-41" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/520806" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">38</figureCitation>
) in lateral view, hand-shaped, anal style slender, lateral lobes distally shorter than anal style, dorsolateral and middle parts each with a finger-like process, basolateral side with a finger-like process. Aedeagus (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 31–41" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 31 - 41. Metanigrus gremius sp. nov., male 31 head and thorax, dorsal view 32 frons, ventral view 33 tegmina 34 wing 35, 38 pygofer, lateral view 36, 39 gonostyli and pygofer, ventral view 37 aedeagus, left lateral view 40 gonostyli, dorsal view 41 aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1024.62226.figures31-41" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/520806" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">35</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 31–41" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 31 - 41. Metanigrus gremius sp. nov., male 31 head and thorax, dorsal view 32 frons, ventral view 33 tegmina 34 wing 35, 38 pygofer, lateral view 36, 39 gonostyli and pygofer, ventral view 37 aedeagus, left lateral view 40 gonostyli, dorsal view 41 aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1024.62226.figures31-41" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/520806" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">37</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 31–41" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 31 - 41. Metanigrus gremius sp. nov., male 31 head and thorax, dorsal view 32 frons, ventral view 33 tegmina 34 wing 35, 38 pygofer, lateral view 36, 39 gonostyli and pygofer, ventral view 37 aedeagus, left lateral view 40 gonostyli, dorsal view 41 aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1024.62226.figures31-41" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/520806" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">38</figureCitation>
, 
