<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="197" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="197">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="197">
The species name is derived from the Latin adjective &quot; 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lv &amp; Chen" authorityYear="2021" class="Insecta" family="Meenoplidae" genus="Metanigrus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Metanigrus gremius" order="Hemiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="197" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gremius">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">Metanigrus gremius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
&quot;, referring to general yellowish white.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="197" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="197">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="197">
This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lv &amp; Chen" authorityYear="2021" class="Insecta" family="Meenoplidae" genus="Metanigrus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Metanigrus guttatus" order="Hemiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="197" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="guttatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">Metanigrus guttatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but differs from the latter in: (1) distal part of tegmina without large, black patch (distal part of tegmina with large, black patch in 
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="M. guttatus" pageId="0" pageNumber="197" rank="species" species="guttatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">M. guttatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); (2) dorsolateral and middle parts of anal tube each with a finger-like process (only dorsolateral part of anal tube with a finger-like process in 
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="M. guttatus" pageId="0" pageNumber="197" rank="species" species="guttatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">M. guttatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); (3) outer process of gonostyli nearly square at apex in lateral view (outer process of gonostyli nearly fan-shaped at apex in lateral view in 
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="M. guttatus" pageId="0" pageNumber="197" rank="species" species="guttatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">M. guttatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
